Move.Name: Attack Order
Move.Description: The user calls upon her swarm and heeds them to charge against you. No matter where you run, they will surround you. Hope you are not allergic to bees.
Move.AdditionalInfo: High Critical.

Move.Name: Bug Bite
Move.Description: The Pokémon nibbles its foe, if it finds something tasty it will eat it in an instant. It may try to eat almost anything.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If the Target Pokémon is holding a berry, the user eats it and gains its effect.

Move.Name: Bug Buzz
Move.Description: The Pokémon uses its wings or part of its body to emit sound waves that harm and affect the target.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Sound Based. Roll 1 Chance Dice to reduce foe's Sp. Defense.

Move.Name: Defend Order
Move.Description: A swarm of bugs flies around the user, creating a barrier to protect this Pokémon from damage.
Move.AdditionalInfo: User Increases its Defense and Sp. Defense.

Move.Name: Fell Stinger
Move.Description: The Pokémon stings the target. If the foe is too weakened to move it absorbs part of its power.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If the foe faints due to damage from this attack increase the user's Strength by 2.

Move.Name: First Impression
Move.Description: The Pokémon makes a dramatic entrance to the battlefield, taking the foe by surprise as to who its opponent really is.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Priority 2. This move will only work the First Round the Pokémon is out in battle. From the second round on it will fail automatically.

Move.Name: Fury Cutter
Move.Description: The Pokémon makes use of its claws or scythes to land as many hits as possible.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Successive Actions.

Move.Name: Heal Order
Move.Description: The Pokémon commands its swarm to bring some healing honey.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Basic Heal.

Move.Name: Infestation
Move.Description: The Pokémon summons a huge swarm of bugs to prevent the foe from escaping. Sometimes the swarm may take a hit to the foe. The call extends for hundreds of yards.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Blocks. Roll 2 Dice of Damage against the foe at the end of each Round. Lasts 4 Rounds.

Move.Name: Leech Life
Move.Description: The user attacks a vital spot and sucks away the vitality of its foe.
Move.AdditionalInfo: The user restores HP equal to half the damage dealt rounded down.

Move.Name: Lunge
Move.Description: The user charges against the foe at full force, not just to knock it down but to restain it with its many limbs.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Reduce foe's Strength.

Move.Name: Megahorn
Move.Description: The Pokémon uses its strong horn(s) to pierce its foe and deal massive damage.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal Damage.

Move.Name: Pin Missile
Move.Description: The Pokémon showers its foe with stings or spikes that pierce like needles.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Successive Actions.

Move.Name: Pollen Puff
Move.Description: The Pokémon creates a puff of pollen that explodes on the foe's face and gives them a terrible allergy. When consumed these puffs are sweet and very nutritious.
Move.AdditionalInfo: When this move is used against an ally it will heal 1 HP instead of dealing damage.

Move.Name: Powder
Move.Description: The foe is fully covered with a flammable powder, a source of fire might ignite it with explosive results.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Add 3 Dice of Damage to the next Fire Type attack that hits the target.

Move.Name: Quiver Dance
Move.Description: A mystical and beautiful dance that boosts a Pokémon's dexterity and focus.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Increases Dexterity, Special, and Sp. Defense.

Move.Name: Rage Powder
Move.Description: The Pokémon releases an irritating powder that annoys and enrages foes into attacking.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Priority 2. During this Round, all damage moves from any foe must target the User.

Move.Name: Signal Beam
Move.Description: The user emits an intense light that harms the foes and may leave them dazed like moths.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 1 Chance Dice to Confuse the foe.

Move.Name: Silver Wind
Move.Description: The Pokémon blows a beautiful silver colered wind that harms the foe, the performance may give the user a big confidence boost.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 1 Chance Dice to Increase User's Strength. Dexterity. Special. Defense. Sp. Defense.

Move.Name: Spider Web
Move.Description: The User quietly releases a web on the field. All foes will be trapped.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Blocks.

Move.Name: Steamroller
Move.Description: The user curls up and rolls at full speed to strike the foe. It may leave the target swatted on the ground.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 3 Chance Dice to Flinch the foe.

Move.Name: Sticky Web
Move.Description: The Pokémon quickly covers the arena with a sticky web, newly arrived foes will have trouble moving with ease.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Entry Hazard. Foe Pokémon that enter the battlefield get a Dexterity Reduction of 1. Pokémon with the Levitate ability and Flying Type Pokémon are immune to this effect.

Move.Name: String Shot
Move.Description: The user shoots a silk string that ties and limits the movement of its foe.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Targets All Foes in Range. Reduce the Dexterity of those affected.

Move.Name: Struggle Bug
Move.Description: The Pokémon lays on its back and struggles with the foe, disrupting the foe's concentration.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Reduce the foe's Special.

Move.Name: Tail Glow
Move.Description: The user emits a strong light. This Pokémon will stare at its brightness to enter a trance.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Increase the User's Special by 3.

Move.Name: Twineedle
Move.Description: The Pokémon stabs the foe with its stinger, claws or spikes infused with poison.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Double action.  Roll 2 Chance Dice to Poison the foe per hit.

Move.Name: U-Turn
Move.Description: The user strikes its foe, then quickly goes back to safety while another party Pokémon takes its place.
Move.AdditionalInfo: The user switches out after dealing damage. The replacement Pokémon arrives to ready to fight. Roll its initiative Switcher Move.

Move.Name: X-Scissor
Move.Description: The Pokémon uses its scythes or claws as if they were a pair of scissors to cut through the foe.

Move.Name: Assurance
Move.Description: The user retaliates against the foe, the rush of adrenaline allows it to hit harder.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If the User has already received damage from the target this Round add 2 Extra Dice to the Damage Pool.

Move.Name: Baddy Bad
Move.Description: The Pokémon acts like a thug and channels its own dark aura as protection for itself and its allies.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If successful, for the next 4 Rounds the User and Allies will receive 1 less damage from Physical Attacks. This effect does not stack. If the user of this Move is at its Final Stage of Evolution, this move fails.

Move.Name: Beat Up
Move.Description: The user calls other Pokémon to aid it in battle, together they give a beating to the foe.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If the attack is successful, add 2 Dice of Damage for every ally Pokémon that spends an action to help the user perform this move. Up to 3 allies may join.

Move.Name: Bite
Move.Description: The user lands a vicious bite that may leave an ugly bruise.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 3 Chance Dice to Flinch the foe.

Move.Name: Brutal Swing
Move.Description: The Pokémon starts attacking at full force with its claws, anyone unfortunate enough to be in its path will end up severely wounded.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. Target all Foes in range.

Move.Name: Crunch
Move.Description: The Pokémon uses its fangs to viciously tear whatever it is biting.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. Roll 1 Chance Dice to reduce foe's Defense.

Move.Name: Dark Pulse
Move.Description: The Pokémon sends a wave of dark feelings that affect those who are most vulnerable, hurting the foe and leaving it unable to act.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Targets random foe. Roll 2 Chance Dice to Flinch the foe.

Move.Name: Dark Void
Move.Description: A portal opens and transports all foes to a world of darkness, inside they can't see or feel anything, it's like they are trapped in an eternal slumber.
Move.AdditionalInfo: All Foes in Range have the Sleep condition.

Move.Name: Darkest Lariat
Move.Description: The user swings both of its arms against the target, there's no armor thick enough to stop the strike.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Ignore the the foe's Attribute Increases that would decrease this Move's damage.

Move.Name: Embargo
Move.Description: The user quickly takes out the held item of a Pokémon. It also empties the bag of the trainer and forces everyone to stay away from their own properties. Evildoers master this Move.
Move.AdditionalInfo: The target cannot use its held item nor can its trainer use items on it.

Move.Name: Fake Tears
Move.Description: The user stops battling and feigns to be crying, disrupting the foe's mood to battle and making it lower its guard.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Reduce the foe's Sp. Defense by 2.

Move.Name: False Surrender
Move.Description: The Pokémon bows in defeat, begging for forgiveness, then backstabs its gullible foe.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Never Fail.

Move.Name: Feint Attack
Move.Description: The Pokémon approaches the foe disarmingly then attacks suddenly without giving any time to react.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Never Fail.

Move.Name: Flatter
Move.Description: The user starts flattering and admiring its opponent. It sure makes it feel good about itself, but why?
Move.AdditionalInfo: Increase the foe's Special. Confuse foe.

Move.Name: Fling
Move.Description: The usr takes its held item and throws it at the opponent. You may get it back after the fight.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Add up to 4 Dice to the Damage Pool, depending on the held item thrown. See P. 432 for more info.

Move.Name: Foul Play
Move.Description: The user feint attacks then tricks the foe who ends up hurting itself.
Move.AdditionalInfo: S.T.A.B of the user and Strength of the foe apply for this move's damage.

Move.Name: Hone Claws
Move.Description: The Pokémon sharpens its claws to perform more precise attacks.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Increase the User's Strength and Accuracy.

Move.Name: Hyperspace Fury
Move.Description: The Pokémon opens portals to attack with each one of its arms, bypassing all defenses and making it impossible to escape, however, the user's defense also gets neglected.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Never Fail. Ignores the effect of any Shield Move the Foe might have used. Reduce the user's Defense.

Move.Name: Jaw Lock
Move.Description: The user will capture its foe in a crushing jaw grip. It won't let go no matter how much you try to seperate them. The only way it will release its victim is by fainting.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Both User and Target are Blocked.

Move.Name: Knock Off
Move.Description: The Pokémon makes a quick tackle that knocks off anything the foe was holding.
Move.AdditionalInfo: The target Pokémon loses its held item.

Move.Name: Memento
Move.Description: The user unleashes all its remaining power to send a wave of hopeless thoughts to haunt the foe's mind and soul. The target will be left in grief.
Move.AdditionalInfo: The user faints. Reduce foe's Strength. Dexterity. Special. Defense and Sp. Defense by 2. Lasts for a whole scene.

Move.Name: Nasty Plot
Move.Description: The Pokémon starts plotting on how to defeat the enemy. Its evil laugh reveals the bad intentions.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Increase the user's Special by 2.

Move.Name: Night Daze
Move.Description: The user forms a pitch black wave that hurts the foe. This darkness may remain obstructing the target's vision.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 4 Chance Dice to Reduce foe's Accuracy.

Move.Name: Night Slash
Move.Description: The user quickly slashes through the target as soon as it gets the chance. The intent to end the target's life is frightening.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. High Critical.

Move.Name: Obstruct
Move.Description: In a reckless action, the user charges against the foe to stop its momentum and block its incoming attack. Being so close allows the user to reach for weak spots.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Priority 4. Shield Move. * If the Foe used a Non- Physical Move against the user, Reduce the Foes Defense by 2.

Move.Name: Parting Shot
Move.Description: The user threatens the foe, leaving it too scared to pursuit the user or overwhelm the ally that just switched in the battlefield.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Reduce foe's Strength and Special. The user switches out, the new Pokémon arrives ready to fight. Roll for its initiative. Switcher Move.

Move.Name: Payback
Move.Description: The Pokémon tackles the target with hatred and vengeance.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Add 2 Extra Dice to the Damage Pool if the target already damaged you this Round.

Move.Name: Power Trip
Move.Description: In the heat of the battle, the Pokémon gets carried away, relishing in its own power.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Add 1 Dice to the Damage Pool of this Move for every Attribute increase the user has. Up to 7 Dice may be added this way. (ie. the user has 2 increased points on Defense, add 2 Damage dice).

Move.Name: Punishment
Move.Description: The user takes advantage of its foe's strengths to use them against it.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Add up to 7 Dice to the Damage Pool for every Increased Attribute the foe has. (ie. Foe has 1 Increased dice in Dexterity & Strength that equals +2 Dice on the Damage Pool of this attack).

Move.Name: Pursuit
Move.Description: The Pokémon chases the foe to deliver a final blow before it escapes.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If the foe is Switching Out or escaping. Add 2 Dice to the Damage Pool and Priority 1 to this move.

Move.Name: Quash
Move.Description: The user represses the foe with intimidation so it has to think twice before acting.
Move.AdditionalInfo: For the rest of the scene, the target will go last in the order of Initiative.

Move.Name: Snarl
Move.Description: The Pokémon viciously snarls showing its teeth. Its menacing look will make the foe cower in fear.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Sound Based. Reduce the foe's Special.

Move.Name: Snatch
Move.Description: The user analyzes the advantages of the foe then makes them their own.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Erase any Increase or Decrease on the foe's Traits, and place them on the User instead.

Move.Name: Sucker Punch
Move.Description: While the foe is preparing its attack, the user takes advantage and strikes.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Priority 1. This move can only be used after the Target rolls a damaging move.

Move.Name: Switcheroo
Move.Description: The user quickly switches the held items before the foe can realize what happened.
Move.AdditionalInfo: User and Foe switch their Held Item. If only one Pokémon is holding an item it gives it away.

Move.Name: Taunt
Move.Description: The user mocks and teases the target to make it attack in a raging fury.
Move.AdditionalInfo: The target Pokémon can only perform Damaging Moves and Evasion actions for the next 4 Rounds.

Move.Name: Thief
Move.Description: The Pokémon strikes its foe and takes the opportunity to steal whatever the target was holding.
Move.AdditionalInfo: The user steals the foe's Held Item.

Move.Name: Throat Chop
Move.Description: A heinous attack to a Pokémon's throat that will leave them unable to make a sound for hours.
Move.AdditionalInfo: The target cannot use any "Sound Based" Move for the rest of the scene.

Move.Name: Topsy-Turvy
Move.Description: The user changes the nature of its target, bad things become good and good things become bad.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Any Decreases on the foe's Attributes become Increases and vice versa.

Move.Name: Torment
Move.Description: The user torments and enrages the foe, making it unable to keep using its strategy.
Move.AdditionalInfo: The target cannot use the same Moves it used during the last Round. Lasts 4 Rounds.

Move.Name: Breaking Swipe
Move.Description: The Pokémon will use its tail to make a long swipe at its foes. A few cracks are heard, and the foe will limp afterwards.
Move.AdditionalInfo: All Foes in Range. Reduce the Strength of those affected.

Move.Name: Clanging Scales
Move.Description: The Pokémon rattles the scales of its armor creating a frightening noise in the area. Some of its scales fall of as a result, leaving some areas exposed.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Sound Based. Reduce User's Defense.

Move.Name: Clangorous Soul
Move.Description: The Pokémon shakes its scales around, to sharpen, shed, and rearrange them. It's a bit rough, but in the end the Pokémon feels more focused for battle.
Move.AdditionalInfo: User deals Damage to itself equal to Half of its total HP rounded down. Increase User's Strength, Dexterity, Special, Defense and Sp. Defense.

Move.Name: Core Enforcer
Move.Description: Zygarde shoots a beam that fractures the target to its core, rendering it unable to sustain even the most basic of its traits.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If successful and the target of this Move has already inflicted damage this Round, remove the Foe's Ability for the rest of the Scene. (Battle Bond, Comatose, Disguise, Multitype, Power Construct, RKS System, Schooling, Stance Change & Shields Down are exceptions)

Move.Name: Draco Meteor
Move.Description: The Pokémon calls a comet that falls from the sky to deal a brutal amount of damage. This feat demands a lot from the user.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. Reduce User's Special by 2.

Move.Name: Dragon Breath
Move.Description: The user lets out a mystical green breath that hinders the movement of anyone it touches.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 3 Chance Dice to Paralyze the foe.

Move.Name: Dragon Claw
Move.Description: The Pokémon uses its strong claws to deliver a fierce tearing blow.

Move.Name: Dragon Dance
Move.Description: The user performs a vigorous and mystical dance that boosts the fighting spirit and reflexes.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Increase the User's Strength and Dexterity.

Move.Name: Dragon Darts
Move.Description: The Pokémon's head is a nest for its less evolved forms, the younglings will sometimes be used as projectiles.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Double Action

Move.Name: Dragon Hammer
Move.Description: The Pokémon swings its body as a hammer and leaves the foe nailed to the cracked ground.

Move.Name: Dragon Pulse
Move.Description: The user opens its mouth and sends a powerful wave of energy.

Move.Name: Dragon Rage
Move.Description: A dual colored flame that always leaves the same burn marks on everything it touches.
Move.AdditionalInfo: This moves always inflicts 2 damage.

Move.Name: Dragon Rush
Move.Description: The user charges rapidly against the foe. The strike may leave thetarget gasping for air.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 2 Chance Dice to Flinch the foe.

Move.Name: Dragon Tail
Move.Description: This Powerful tail strike can knockdown anyone up to 100 feet away!
Move.AdditionalInfo: Low Priority 1. The target is hit and knocked back to its trainer, stunned. Forcing the trainer to send another Pokémon. In the wild the target is sent away. Switcher Move.

Move.Name: Dual Chop
Move.Description: The Pokémon strikes the foe with brutal blows.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Double Action.

Move.Name: Dynamax Cannon
Move.Description: The Pokémon shoots a heavy projectile, if the foe is under the effects of the Dynamax phenomenon all the energy will be concentrated and explode on the target.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If the Foe is under the effects of Dynamax, This Move becomes Lethal and you add 4 Extra Dice to the Damage Pool.

Move.Name: Eternabeam
Move.Description: The Pokémon shoots an incredibly powerful beam towards the sky. The energy released might keep traveling through space thousands of years later.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. Must Recharge.

Move.Name: Outrage
Move.Description: The user awakens their primal instinct as a dragon and unleashes its uncontrollable fury, destroying everything in its path. After that, the Pokémon is left disoriented and confused.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Rampage.

Move.Name: Roar Of Time
Move.Description: Through a terrifying roar, Dialga bounds the forces of time on a single area, the unfortunate target will be trapped in a time warp, growing old in a matter of seconds.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. If successful, the target can't have any action until next Round.

Move.Name: Spacial Rend
Move.Description: With a flicker of its claws, Palkia defragments the space around its foe. Those who survive rarely do peserve their original shape.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. High Critical.

Move.Name: Twister
Move.Description: The Pokémon lets out a spiral current that surrounds the foes. They can't move until they free themselves from this terrible whirlwind.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 2 Chance Dice to Flinch the foes.

Move.Name: Aura Wheel
Move.Description: The Pokemon happily runs into a wheel made of electricity that strikes the foe. If the user is feeling hungry the wheel's energy is replaced by a dark aura.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If successful, Increase user's Dexterity. If the user is in “Hangry” Form this Move is considered to be Dark-Type.

Move.Name: Bolt Beak
Move.Description: The Pokemon charges with its beak and pecks its foe, if the foe is not fast it will be zapped by a jolt of electricity.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If the Target hasn't had a Turn this Round, add 2 Extra Dice to the Damage pool.

Move.Name: Bolt Strike
Move.Description: Zekrom delivers a powerful tackle while discharging lightning through its body. The foe is rendered unable to move, either by the strike or the electricity
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 2 Chance Dice to Paralyze the foe.

Move.Name: Buzzy Buzz
Move.Description: The Pokemon releases a jolt of static electricity from its fur, that makes a cute zapping sound. It's all fun and games until somebody gets paralyzed.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Paralyze the foe. If the user of this Move is at its Final Stage of Evolution, this move fails.

Move.Name: Charge
Move.Description: The user concentrates all the electricity in its body to be released.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Add 2 Dice to the Damage Pool to the next Electric Damaging move the user performs.

Move.Name: Charge Beam
Move.Description: The Pokemon lets out an electric beam then uses the remaining charge to boost its power.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 5 Chance Dice to Increase the User's Special.

Move.Name: Discharge
Move.Description: The user releases its stored electricity in all directions.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 3 Chance Dice to Paralyze those affected.

Move.Name: Eerie Impulse
Move.Description: The user radiates electricity around itself, the foe will think twice about attacking.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Reduce foe's Special by 2.

Move.Name: Electric Terrain
Move.Description: The user electrifies the terrain, making it impossible to get a good night's sleep on it.
Move.AdditionalInfo: For the Next 4 Rounds all Electric Attacks will deal 1 Extra Dice of Damage. Anyone on the ground will be cured from "Sleep" Status.

Move.Name: Electrify
Move.Description: The user hurls an electric projectile to the target, the foe is charged with electricity until it is released by the foe's next attack.
Move.AdditionalInfo: The Damage from the next attack made by the target will be Electric Type.

Move.Name: Electro Ball
Move.Description: The Pokemon creates a small electricity orb that is hurled at the target. If the user is faster, the impact will be bigger.
Move.AdditionalInfo: The user adds 1 Dice to the Damage Pool for every Dexterity point the User has that surpasses the foe's. Up to 4 Dice may be added.

Move.Name: Electroweb
Move.Description: Shoots an electrified web at all foes to restrict their movement. Walking through this web can be painful.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Reduce Dexterity of those affected.

Move.Name: Fusion Bolt
Move.Description: The Pokemon strikes with a devastating electric impact, said impact will grow larger and stronger if there's a special kind of fire nearby.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. If the Move “Fusion Flare” has already been used by anyone this Round, add 4 Extra Dice to the Damage Pool of this Move.

Move.Name: Ion Deluge
Move.Description: The user amplifies all electrically charged particles in the environment. The results are shocking!
Move.AdditionalInfo: For the rest of the Scene, Normal Type Moves will deal damage as if they were Electric Type Moves.

Move.Name: Magnet Rise
Move.Description: The Pokemon uses the magnetic field of the earth to repel itself from the ground, allowing it to float for a short period of time.
Move.AdditionalInfo: For the Next 4 Rounds the User gains immunity against Ground Type Moves.

Move.Name: Magnetic Flux
Move.Description: The Pokemon bends the magnetic field around itself, this also affects all allies who are sensible to it.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Increase the Defense and Sp. Defense of User and all its Electric and Steel Type Allies.

Move.Name: Nuzzle
Move.Description: The Pokemon rubs its electrified cheeks against the foe, it looks very cute but it can be dangerous.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Paralyze the foe.

Move.Name: Overdrive
Move.Description: The Pokemon uses its own body as an amplifier for the energizing sounds it produces.
Move.AdditionalInfo: All Foes in Range. Sound Based.

Move.Name: Parabolic Charge
Move.Description: The Pokemon lets go of a big electric charge from its body. The charge comes back to it even bigger.
Move.AdditionalInfo: The user restores HP equal to half the damage dealt to one target, rounded down.

Move.Name: Pika Papow
Move.Description: The User lets out its energy in the form of a lightning strike, the happier the user feels the more energized it will be.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Add 1 Die to the Damage Roll for every point of Happiness on the User. If the user of this Move is at its Final Stage of Evolution, this move fails.

Move.Name: Plasma Fists
Move.Description: The user charges its fists with electricity, and upon impact the charge materializes into plasma that adds an electric element to all of its Normal moves.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Fist Based. If successful, all Normal-Type Moves of the user will be considered Electric Type until the end of the Scene.

Move.Name: Shock Wave
Move.Description: The user quickly releases jolts of electricity that are too fast for many to react.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Never Fail.

Move.Name: Spark
Move.Description: The user tackles the foe, releasing a powerful spark on contact.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 3 Chance Dice to Paralyze the foe.

Move.Name: Thunder
Move.Description: The Pokemon commands a tremendous lightning to strike a specific point on the ground. It's quite dangerous.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. Roll 3 Chance Dice to Paralyze foe. If performed under Sunny Weather, Accuracy becomes -3 instead. If performed under Rain Weather, Ignore this Moves Reduced Accuracy.

Move.Name: Thunder Fang
Move.Description: The user lands an electrified bite on the foe. The direct current may affect the foe greatly.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 2 Chance Dice to Flinch the foe. Roll 2 Chance Dice to Paralyze the foe.

Move.Name: Thunder Punch
Move.Description: An Electrified punch to deal a shocking blow.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Fist Based. Roll 1 Chance Dice to Paralyze foe.

Move.Name: Thunder Shock
Move.Description: A small electric attack that shocks the foe and may leave it with muscular cramps. Some electric devices hit by this attack will malfunction.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 1 Chance Dice to Paralyze the foe.

Move.Name: Thunder Wave
Move.Description: A tide of bright lightning streams from the floor onto the foe. The target's body will be cramped for hours.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Paralyze the foe.

Move.Name: Thunderbolt
Move.Description: A strong electric attack that shocks and harms the foe. It can destroy most kinds of electric equipment.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 1 Chance Dice to Paralyze the foe.

Move.Name: Volt Switch
Move.Description: The User quickly shoots an electic jolt, then switches places with an awaiting Pokemon partner at the speed of lightning.
Move.AdditionalInfo: The user switches out after dealing damage. The new Pokémon arrives ready to fight on the next Round. Switcher Move.

Move.Name: Volt Tackle
Move.Description: The user surrounds itself with big bolts of electricity, then it crashes against the foe.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Recoil. Roll 1 Chance Dice to Paralyze the Foe.

Move.Name: Wild Charge
Move.Description: The Pokemon surrounds itself with wild botls of lightning, then tackles recklessly.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Recoil.

Move.Name: Zap Cannon
Move.Description: The user hurls a dreadful bombardment of electric explosions. Anyone hit won't be able to move for a very long time.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. Paralyze the Foe.

Move.Name: Zing Zap
Move.Description: The user hurls itself as a zig-zaging ball of electricity that explodes on contact, this leaves the foe unable to move for a few seconds.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 3 Chance Dice to Flinch the Foe.

Move.Name: Zippy Zap
Move.Description: The user zips and zaps from one place to another to strike the foe moving so fast it appears to be teleporting, leaving almost no time to react.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Priority 2. This Move is always a Critical Hit and gets the proper Bonus for it. If the user of this Move is at its Final Stage of Evolution, this move fails.

Move.Name: Aromatic Mist
Move.Description: The Pokemon showers an ally in a mist with a revitalizing armoa.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Increase one Ally's Defense and Sp. Defense.

Move.Name: Baby-Doll Eyes
Move.Description: Before anyone acts in battle, the user looks at the foe with the cutest eyes.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Priority 1. Reduce foe's Strength.

Move.Name: Charm
Move.Description: The Pokemon uses a cute and harmless attitude to make the foe less wary and aggresive.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Reduce foe's Strength by 2.

Move.Name: Crafty Shield
Move.Description: The Pokemon creates a magic shield to protect everyone from the bad tricks a foe might have under its sleeve. Under this shield, everyone can see dishonesty and bad intentions.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Priority 3. The User and its Allies are protected from the effects of a Support Move. Shield.

Move.Name: Dazzling Gleam
Move.Description: The user shines a powerful flash that hurts the eyes of everyone watching it.

Move.Name: Decorate
Move.Description: Using some frosting the Pokemon decorates their target to look bigger, more powerful, and incredibly delicious!
Move.AdditionalInfo: Increase the Strength and Special of One Ally by 2

Move.Name: Disarming Voice
Move.Description: With a charming and manipulative cry, the user deals emotional damage to its opponent. This move always makes the target feel bad.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Sound Based. Never Fail. Targets All foes in range.

Move.Name: Draining Kiss
Move.Description: The user sends a kiss with a flirty intention, the foe catches the kiss but it ends up draining the target's energy.
Move.AdditionalInfo: The User restores HP equal to half the damage dealt, rounded down.

Move.Name: Fairy Lock
Move.Description: The user moves as if locking a door. It takes a few moments before everyone realizes that they are not really trapped.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Blocks. Last 1 Round.

Move.Name: Fairy Wind
Move.Description: The Pokemon strikes with a wind covered in fairy dust. It causes itching.

Move.Name: Fleur Cannon
Move.Description: A light beam pierces the battlefield, it deals devastating damage but leaves newly grown flowers instead of scorched earth. The user is left feeling very tired.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. Reduce User's Special by 2.

Move.Name: Floral Healing
Move.Description: The user creates a flower crown that heals and relaxes its wearer. Under the right conditions this move also creates a flower patch around its target.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Basic Heal. If performed over Grassy Terrain this move is a Complete Heal.

Move.Name: Flower Shield
Move.Description: The Pokemon uses a mysterious power that causes flowers to bloom beneath every Grass Pokemon nearby. Flora in this field is more resilient and beautiful.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Increase the Defense of All Grass Type Pokémon on the field.

Move.Name: Geomancy
Move.Description: Through a mystical connection this Pokemon absorbs the life force of earth itself to increase its power.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Charge Move. The user charges, then Increases by 2 its Dexterity, Special and Sp. Defense scores on its next Turn.

Move.Name: Light Of Ruin
Move.Description: By drawing energy from the Eternal Flower, the Pokemon unleashes all of its hurt. A beautiful light surrounds the area, yet the pain inside of its heart remains.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. Recoil.

Move.Name: Misty Terrain
Move.Description: The user surrounds the battlefield with a mystical mist that feels protective. Mythical Pokemon find something eerie about it.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Creatures standing on the battlefield won't be affected by Status Ailments. Dragon Type attacks won't add their Power to the Damage Pool. Lasts 4 Rounds.

Move.Name: Moonblast
Move.Description: Summon power directly from the moon. The Pokemon blasts the foe with light.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 3 Chance Dice to Reduce foe's Special.

Move.Name: Moonlight
Move.Description: The user gathers power from the light of the moon, the energy absorbed can heal most injuries.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Basic Heal. If successful spend 1 Will point to activate. If performed at Night or Sunny Weather is in effect this move becomes a Complete Heal. If Rain/Sandstorm Weather is in effect this move only heals 1 HP

Move.Name: Nature's Madness
Move.Description: The forces of nature attack as if they had a will of their own. Water will try to drown you, plants will trap you, lightning will come out of nowhere, and even your own body will fail you.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Damage Roll is Half of the Foe's remaining HP (up to 10) Rounded down. If the remaining HP of the foe is 1, this move fails. Ignore the foe's Defenses.

Move.Name: Play Rough
Move.Description: The user and the foe start a playful wrestle, it soon escalates into something not so pretty.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 1 Chance Dice to Reduce foe's Strength.

Move.Name: Sparkly Swirl
Move.Description: The Pokemon unleashes a swirling and glittery energy that releases a pleasant aroma that soothes the body and has healing properties.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If successful, heal any Status Ailment on the User and Allies. If the user of this Move is at its Final Stage of Evolution, this move fails.

Move.Name: Spirit Break
Move.Description: Sometimes words hurt a lot more than blows. With this Move the Pokemon deals both.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If successful, reduce the Foe's Special.

Move.Name: Strange Steam
Move.Description: The user releases an addictive sweet-smelling steam, do not be fooled as it is toxic and has nasty side-effects.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 2 Chance Dice to Confuse the Foe.

Move.Name: Sweet Kiss
Move.Description: The Pokemon moves towards the foe and plants a delicate kiss on its cheek, then leaves playfully. The foe struggles to know what it meant.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Confuse the foe.

Move.Name: Arm Thrust
Move.Description: The user quickly throws blows of open-palmed thrusts against the foe.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Successive Actions.

Move.Name: Aura Sphere
Move.Description: The user channels its aura and launches this power in the form of a sphere The foe's aura is hit, leaving the target unscratched but deeply hurt.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Never Fail.

Move.Name: Body Press
Move.Description: The Pokémon makes a judo maneuver, using its body mass instead of its strength against the target.

Move.Name: Brick Break
Move.Description: The Pokémon uses its palm or claws to perform a one-armed chop that shatters even invisible barriers.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If a Barrier is in place on the foe's side (ie. Light Screen, Reflect) destroy the barrier and add 2 Extra Dice to the Damage Pool.

Move.Name: Bulk Up
Move.Description: The Pokémon shows its muscles with intimidating poses to look bigger and stronger.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Increase the User's Strength and Defense.

Move.Name: Circle Throw
Move.Description: The user throws the target 60 feet out of the battlefield.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Low Priority 1. The target is hit and knocked back to its trainer forcing them to send out another Pokémon. In the wild the target is sent away. Switcher Move.

Move.Name: Close Combat
Move.Description: The user attacks at a close distance to deal lots of damage. The foe is also close enough to attack.
Move.AdditionalInfo: After dealing damage, Reduce the User's Defense and Sp. Defense.

Move.Name: Counter
Move.Description: The user prepares to receive damage, then returns the same damage and more.
Move.AdditionalInfo: This Move can only deal damage if the Foe has dealt Physical Damage to the User this Round. Roll the same Damage Pool as your Foe plus 2 Extra Dice. Ignore the foe's Defenses.

Move.Name: Cross Chop
Move.Description: The user delivers a chop with its arms crossed trying to hot a weak spot.
Move.AdditionalInfo: High Critical.

Move.Name: Detect
Move.Description: The user detects the intentions of the attacker and acts out to minimize the damage.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Priority. Shield Move. Reduce 3 Damage this pokemon would receive from a Damaging Move. Negate effects of Support Moves that target the user. Reduce to zero the set damage from a move the user would take.

Move.Name: Double Kick
Move.Description: The user throws two powerful kicks.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Double Action.

Move.Name: Drain Punch
Move.Description: The Pokémon strikes with a powerful punch. Through contact, it absorbs some vital energy.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Fist Based. The user restore HP equal to half the damage dealt, rounded down.

Move.Name: Dynamic Punch
Move.Description: A punch that hits a small pressure point. It leavers the foe disoriented.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Fist Based. Confuse the foe.

Move.Name: Final Gambit
Move.Description: The Pokémon puts its last strength into an all-or-nothing attack. After that, it faints.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Ignore the foe's Defenses. The user faints after dealing damage.

Move.Name: Flying Press
Move.Description: The user flies towards the foe from the sky in pure Lucha Libre style.
Move.AdditionalInfo: When Dealing damage with this move, it counts as if this move was also Flying Type.

Move.Name: Focus Blast
Move.Description: The user concentrates and releases a blast of energy.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 1 Chance Dice to Reduce foe's Sp. Defense.

Move.Name: Focus Punch
Move.Description: A brutal punch that requires calm and concentration
Move.AdditionalInfo: Fist Based. Charge Move. The User will flinch if it gets hit before releasing this attack.

Move.Name: Force Palm
Move.Description: A powerful open palm hit that knocks the foe away and may leave him unable to move.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 3 Chance Dice to Paralyze the foe.

Move.Name: Hammer Arm
Move.Description: A mighty arm thrust that leaves the user quite tired.
Move.AdditionalInfo: After dealing damage, Reduce user's Dexterity.

Move.Name: High Jump Kick
Move.Description: The user launches itself up and falls down with a brutal kick. It might hurt the user if it doesn't hit the target.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If Accuracy Roll is unsuccessful, deal 5 Dice of Damage to the User.

Move.Name: Jump Kick
Move.Description: The Pokémon jumps and delivers a powerful kick. It might hurt the user if it doesn't hit the target.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If Accuracy Roll is unsuccessful, deal 4 Dice of Damage to the User.

Move.Name: Karate Chop
Move.Description: A basic fighting chop that has been practiced and mastered.
Move.AdditionalInfo: High Critical.

Move.Name: Low Kick
Move.Description: The user kicks the target making it fall, the bigger the foe the harder the fall.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Add 1 Extra Dice to the Damage Pool for every 50 kgs. of weight on the foe. Up to +4 Extra Dice may be added this way.

Move.Name: Low Sweep
Move.Description: The Pokémon strikes the foe's legs, leaving it unable to walk normally or run.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Reduce Foe's Dexterity by 2.

Move.Name: Mach Punch
Move.Description: The user launches a punch so quickly that it's barely seen.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Fist Based. Priority 1.

Move.Name: Mat Block
Move.Description: The Pokémon uses a mat or something similar as a shield.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Shield. Reduce 3 Dice from the foe's Damage Pool. This Move only works the first Round the User has been out.

Move.Name: Meteor Assault
Move.Description: The Pokémon will make an incredible jump to the sky, then lunge towards the foe at a staggering speed, crashing the ground upon impact. The user is left very tired.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. Must Recharge.

Move.Name: No Retreat
Move.Description: No surrender. No retreat. Until victory always.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Increase the User's Strength, Dexterity, Special, Defense and Sp. Defense. The user is now blocked.

Move.Name: Octolock
Move.Description: The user wraps its tentacles to immobilize the foe. Being so close enables the user to find weak spots.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Block. Reduce the foe's Defense and Sp. Defense.

Move.Name: Power-Up Punch
Move.Description: The Pokémon uses this punch to test the surface of an object. The user toughens up to deal better blows.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Fist Based. Increase User's Strength.

Move.Name: Quick Guard
Move.Description: The user reacts instinctively and defends itself and its teammates, nullifying the effects of the fastest attacks.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Priority 3. Shield Move. This move will only protect against Damaging Moves with "Priority". Reduce 3 Dice from the foe's Damage Pool. Negate the effects of support moves that target the User and Allies.

Move.Name: Revenge
Move.Description: The Pokémon fights ruthlessly and may retaliate fiercely against a foe that has hurt the user.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If the User has already received damage this round, add 2 Extra Dice to the Damage Pool.

Move.Name: Reversal
Move.Description: The user gathers its mettle to block away the pain and focus on hitting harder.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Add 1 Extra Dice to the Damage Pool for every missing HP the User has. Up to 5 Dice may be added this Way.

Move.Name: Rock Smash
Move.Description: A powerful hit that can crush rocks. Used against a foe it is sure to leave an awful bruise and a crack on its armor.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 5 Chance Dice to Reduce foe's Defense.

Move.Name: Rolling Kick
Move.Description: The user spins in the air landing an impressive kick that may daze the target.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 3 Chance Dice to Flinch the Foe.

Move.Name: Sacred Sword
Move.Description: The user slashes its target with a mighty blade that no armor can stop.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Ignore any Increases to the foe's Defense.

Move.Name: Secret Sword
Move.Description: An invisible wave cuts through the target, you can feel its sharp edge but you cannot see it.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Apply the foe's Defense instead of its Sp. Defense to resist Damage from this Move

Move.Name: Seismic Toss
Move.Description: The target gets launched up then falls face first into the ground, the stronger the user the higher the foe will be thrown.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll Damage Dice according to the User's Rank. 1 Dice at Starter Rank. 2 Dice at Beginner Rank.  3 dice at Amateur Rank.  4 Dice at Ace Rank.  5 Dice at Professional Rank. Ignores Defense.

Move.Name: Sky Uppercut
Move.Description: The user attacks with an uppercut, throwing the foe skyward with lots of force.

Move.Name: Storm Throw
Move.Description: The user impacts a weak spot with a powerful blow.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If the Accuracy Roll is successful this move becomes a Critical Hit.

Move.Name: Submission
Move.Description: The user recklessly struggles with the foe to pin it to the ground.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Recoil.

Move.Name: Superpower
Move.Description: The Pokémon makes use of all its force to deliver a crushing strike to the foe, this demands a lot from the user.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. Reduce User's Strength and Defense.

Move.Name: Triple Kick
Move.Description: The user throws three or more kicks, leaving the harder blow for the end.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Successive Actions. Add 1 Extra Dice to Damage Pool to the last kick performed.

Move.Name: Vacuum Wave
Move.Description: The user pulls the enemy closer using the power of its ki. This traction has a lot of strength and may break anything it pulls.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Priority 1.

Move.Name: Vital Throw
Move.Description: The Pokémon awaits for the perfect moment to strike the foe.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Low Priority 1. Never Fail.

Move.Name: Wake-Up Slap
Move.Description: A powerful slap that makes even the laziest Pokémon be well awake.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If the Foe is sleeping, Add 2 Extra Dice to the Damage Pool. The foe Wakes up afterwards.

Move.Name: Blast Burn
Move.Description: The Pokemon uses all of its power to deliver an infernal blast to the foe. The user is left exhausted.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. Must Recharge.

Move.Name: Blaze Kick
Move.Description: The user throws a mighty kick engulfed in fire that may leave a bad looking burn.
Move.AdditionalInfo: High Critical. Roll 2 Chance Dice to Apply Burn 2 to the Foe.

Move.Name: Blue Flare
Move.Description: Reshiram surrounds itself with a giant blue flame that is unleashed with an earth shattering explosion. Receiving this attack directly might completely engulf you in fire.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 2 Chance Dice to Apply Burn 3 to the foe.

Move.Name: Burn Up
Move.Description: The User unleashes all of its might through a massive blast of raging fire. Although the damage is devastating the Pokemon is left unable to produce more fire for at least a day.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. After Damage is dealt, the user is no longer considered a Fire-Type for the rest of the day (if its only type was Fire, it is now considered Typeless). Fire-type Moves won't add their Power to the Damage pool of this Pokémon for the rest of the day.

Move.Name: Ember
Move.Description: The user shoots a small flame against the target that may cause a first-degree burn.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 1 Chance Dice to Burn the foe.

Move.Name: Eruption
Move.Description: A fierce burst of lava coming from the user at full force charring whatever comes in contact with it.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. Reduce 1 Dice from the Damage Pool for every missing HP the User has. Up to 5 dice may be removed this way.

Move.Name: Fiery Dance
Move.Description: The user cloaks itself in flames and shoots them while dancing gracefully.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 5 Chance Dice to Increase the User's Special.

Move.Name: Fire Blast
Move.Description: The Pokemon shoots a giant fireball that explodes on contact with the foe, blasting fire in all directions.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. Roll 3 Chance Dice to apply Burn 3 to the foe.

Move.Name: Fire Fang
Move.Description: The user breathes fire from its mouth while biting the target.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 2 Chance to Flinch the Foe. Roll 2 Chance Dice to Burn the foe.

Move.Name: Fire Lash
Move.Description: With a whip of fire, the Pokemon ensnares its foe, who is left defenseless and at its mercy.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Reduce Foe's Defense.

Move.Name: Fire Pledge
Move.Description: The Pokemon chants to invoke the power of Fire. Its pledge is heard, then the flames consume everything around.
Move.AdditionalInfo: All flammable plants and objects in the battlefield are covered in flames. Roll 1 Dice of Fire Damage at the end of every Round against everyone on the field.

Move.Name: Fire Punch
Move.Description: The User can ignite its fists for a brief moment without any danger of getting burned. The foe may not be so lucky.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Fist Based. Roll 1 Chance Dice to apply Burn 2 to the foe.

Move.Name: Fire Spin
Move.Description: The user creates a vortex of fire that remains spinning in the battlefield, trapping the foe within.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Blocks. Roll 2 Dice of Damage against the foe at the end of each Round. Lasts 4 Rounds.

Move.Name: Flame Burst
Move.Description: A concentrated flameball that bursts on contact with the foe, scattering smaller flames around.
Move.AdditionalInfo: After dealing damage, the user may roll 1 Dice of Damage against two other Targets.

Move.Name: Flame Charge
Move.Description: The Pokemon uses its flames as propulsion to strike the foe.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Increase the User's Dexterity.

Move.Name: Flame Wheel
Move.Description: The user cloaks itself in flames and rolls to tackle the target.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 1 Chance Dice to Burn the foe.

Move.Name: Flamethrower
Move.Description: The user lets out a powerful fire stream that leaves a scorched trail.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 1 Chance Dice to Apply Burn 2 to the foe.

Move.Name: Flare Blitz
Move.Description: The user sets itself on fire, recklessly charging against the target with a brutal strike.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Recoil. Roll 1 Chance Dice to Apply Burn 3 to the foe.

Move.Name: Fusion Flare
Move.Description: The Pokemon sets ablaze a swirling pillar upon the target, said pillar will grow taller and swirl faster if there's a special kind of charge nearby.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. If the Move “Fusion Bolt” has already been used by anyone this Round, add 4 Extra Dice to the Damage Pool of this Move

Move.Name: Heat Crash
Move.Description: The user slams the target with a body engulfed in fire.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Add 1 Extra Dice to the Damage Pool for every 50 kgs. of weight above the target's weight. Up to +4 Extra Dice may be added this way.

Move.Name: Heat Wave
Move.Description: The user breathes a giant wave of incandescent air that might set fire to whatever it touches.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Target all foes in Range. Roll 1 Chance Dice to Burn those affected.

Move.Name: Incinerate
Move.Description: The Pokemon releases a blast of fire that instantly consumes small flammable objects.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Destroy the held Berries of those affected.

Move.Name: Inferno
Move.Description: The Pokemon sets the foe on fire. These flames rise up to 6 feet. A very dangerous Move.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. Apply Burn 3 to the Foe.

Move.Name: Lava Plume
Move.Description: The user shoots up bits of molten lava that fall scattered around the field.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 3 Chance Dice to Burn those affected.

Move.Name: Magma Storm
Move.Description: The Pokemon shoots a fiery eruption to its foe. Unable to escape and surrounded by the unbearable heat the foe's survival is at risk.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Blocks. Roll 3 Damage Dice at the end of each Round. Lasts 4 Rounds.

Move.Name: Mind Blown
Move.Description: The Pokemon has had a terrible day and has a very bad headache, try not to disturb its peace because its head feels like exploding.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Area Attack. Recoil.

Move.Name: Mystical Fire
Move.Description: This mystical fire not only burns the foe, it also drains its power.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Reduce Foe's Special.

Move.Name: Overheat
Move.Description: A furious wave of scorching fire that will turn to ashes everything it touches, exhausting the user afterwards.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. Reduce User's Special by 2.

Move.Name: Pyro Ball
Move.Description: The Pokemon lights a heavy stone on fire and kicks it while it's ablaze. The hit is pretty heavy already, the fire is just for showing off.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 1 Chance Dice to Apply Burn 2 to the Foe.

Move.Name: Sacred Fire
Move.Description: A blazing pillar of rainbow-colored flames crashes upon the foe, it burns and cleanses the evil from within. Those with a pure heart should not fear for they'll be unharmed.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. Roll 5 Chance Dice to Apply Burn 3 to the Foe.

Move.Name: Searing Shot
Move.Description: The User torches everything around itself in a sudden burst of scarlet flames. Everything is brought to cinders in a matter of seconds.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. All Foes in Range. Roll 3 Chance Dice to Apply Burn 2 those Affected.

Move.Name: Shell Trap
Move.Description: It apparently just buries underground, but secretely the Pokemon prepares its shell to detonate; anyone who steps on it will be blown to pieces.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Low Priority 3. This Move strikes the next time the user is hit with a Non- Physical attack.

Move.Name: Sizzly Slide
Move.Description: The user slides on the floor as if it was ice-skating, only there is no ice, only a raging fire.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If the user of this Move is at its Final Stage of Evolution, this move fails. Burn the Foe.

Move.Name: Sunny Day
Move.Description: The Pokemon will raise the temperature along with the sun, it doesn't work at night, indoors, underground, or underwater.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Sunny Weather is activated for the next 4 Rounds.

Move.Name: V-Create
Move.Description: The user slams its foe with a V-Shaped flame on its forehead. Upon impact, it detonates a terrible explosion and leaves the user pretty vulnerable afterwards.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Reduce the user's Dexterity, Defense, and Sp. Defense.

Move.Name: Will-O-Wisp
Move.Description: The user calls a floating ember to consume the foe.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Burn the Foe.

Move.Name: Acrobatics
Move.Description: The user makes quick and graceful acrobatic moves to hit the foe, it will be swifter if nothing gets in the way.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If the User has a Held Item, remove 2 Dice from the Damage Roll.

Move.Name: Aerial Ace
Move.Description: The Pokemon rises up in the air towards a light source, momentarily blinding the foe, then plummets quickly to attack the opponent.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Never Fail.

Move.Name: Aeroblast
Move.Description: The victim is trapped in a violently swirling vortex. The strong wind currents make debris fly everywhere.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. High Critical.

Move.Name: Air Cutter
Move.Description: The user will send out a wave of sharp wind that will harm anything it touches.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Target all foes in Range. High Critical.

Move.Name: Air Slash
Move.Description: The user will surround the foe with razor-like wind that may knock it down.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 3 Chance Dice to Flinch the foe.

Move.Name: Beak Blast
Move.Description: The Pokemon gets ready to release a boiling gas through its beak, which gets incredibly hot. The resulting blast sounds like a train's horn.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Charge Move. Low Priority 3. If the User is hit by a Non  Physical Attack while this move is charging, apply Burn 2 to the foe.

Move.Name: Bounce
Move.Description: The Pokemon will jump 30 feet in the air before landing on top of the foe. The user won't suffer any falling damage.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Charge Move. While charging this Move, the user will be out of range. Roll 3 Chance Dice to Paralyze the foe.

Move.Name: Brave Bird
Move.Description: The Pokemon flies straight at the foe at full speed, the collision might hurt both of them.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Recoil.

Move.Name: Chatter
Move.Description: The user starts talking and giving orders in human language. It may be extremely confusing for the foes.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 3 Chance Dice to Confuse the foe. Sound based move.

Move.Name: Defog
Move.Description: A strong current of wind that blows away any fog and even invisible barriers.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Remove all Barriers (ie. Light Screen, Reflect), Entry Hazards (Toxic Spikes, Stealth Rock, etc.), and Terrains (Misty Terrain, Electric Terrain, etc.) from the battlefield.

Move.Name: Dragon Ascent
Move.Description: The user rises above the clouds and then comes crashing down against its foe in an instant. The strike is brutal for both.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. Reduce the user's Defense and Sp. Defense.

Move.Name: Drill Peck
Move.Description: The user pierces the foe with its beak used as a drill. A dangerous move.

Move.Name: Feather Dance
Move.Description: A beautiful dance that soothes the hearts of those who watch it, reducing their aggressive intentions.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Reduce the foe's Strength by 2.

Move.Name: Floaty Fall
Move.Description: With the help of some air balloons, the user jumps up high and falls on top of its foe. The use of balloons in-battle is questionable, but the referee will allow them.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 3 Chance Dice to Flinch the Foe. If the user of this Move is at its Final Stage of Evolution, this move fails.

Move.Name: Fly
Move.Description: The user flies up high in one action, then drops and strikes in the next one. The Pokemon can fly for extremely long periods of time without getting tired.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Charge Move. While charging this move the User will be out of range, with the exception of the attacks Hurricane and Thunder.

Move.Name: Gust
Move.Description: The Pokemon flaps its wings to strike the foe with wind.

Move.Name: Hurricane
Move.Description: The user attacks by wrapping the opponent in a fierce wind that carries the target up into the sky.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. Roll 3 Chance Dice to Confuse the Foe. If Rain Weather in effect ignore this moves reduced accuracy.

Move.Name: Mirror Move
Move.Description: The user concentrates and manages to imitate the last move used by the foe.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Copies the last Damaging Move the foe has performed.

Move.Name: Oblivion Wing
Move.Description: A dark wind rises, turning everything it touches into dust to be scattered until nothing remains. People, Pokemon, plants, everything fades until a distant memory.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. High Critical.

Move.Name: Peck
Move.Description: The Pokemon uses its beak or horn to jab the foe, hurting a little bit.

Move.Name: Pluck
Move.Description: The user gives a hard peck and may get something tasty out of the foe.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If the Target is holding a Berry, the User eats it and gains its effects.

Move.Name: Roost
Move.Description: The Pokemon uses its action to land on the ground and relax.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Basic Heal. Until the User's next action this Pokémon will be vulnerable to Ground Type moves.

Move.Name: Sky Attack
Move.Description: The Pokemon darts from the sky with a graceful and lethal strike, propelling with the wind, crushing the foe to the ground.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. High Critical. Charge Move. Roll 3 Chance Dice to Flinch the foe.

Move.Name: Sky Drop
Move.Description: The user carries the opponent to the sky, then drops the target from that altitude.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Charge Move. While charging this move the Target is flinched. Flying Type Pokémon are immune to the Damage of this move. Lifting a target is restricted by the Strength of the User.

Move.Name: Tailwind
Move.Description: User flaps its wings and casts a turbulent wind that helps the team move significantly faster.
Move.AdditionalInfo: For the Next 4 Rounds, Increase the Dexterity of the User and All Allies in the field by 2.

Move.Name: Wing Attack
Move.Description: The user flies towards the foe and strikes with its wings.

Move.Name: Astonish
Move.Description: The user sneaks close and startles the foe.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 3 Chance Dice to Flinch the foe.

Move.Name: Confuse Ray
Move.Description: The user flashes a sinister ray of bright light that leaves the target disoriented and confused.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Confuse the foe.

Move.Name: Curse
Move.Description: The user mutters words that become an evil incantation, the curse may only be lifted by a medium or through divine intervention.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll half the user's HP as damage dice to itself, ignoring Defenses. The target will remove 1 success from all their rolls until the Curse is lifted.

Move.Name: Curse (Non-Ghost User)
Move.Description: The Pokemon prepares to deal and receive damage by muttering something not appropriate for kids.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Increase the User's Strength and Defense. Reduce the User's Dexterity. This effect is only for Pokémon who are not Ghost-Type.

Move.Name: Destiny Bond
Move.Description: The Pokemon creates a mystical bond with anyone that causes it harm. Whatever ill falls on the user, it falls on the perpetrator too.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If the user faints this Round due to Combat damage, the Pokémon that dealt the damage will faint at the same time.

Move.Name: Grudge
Move.Description: The user leaves an imprinting grudge over the foe, this makes the target unwilling to fight. It may only keep battling if something greater is at risk.
Move.AdditionalInfo: The User Faints. The foe gets its Will depleted and any effects gained from spending them. The Foe must roll Loyalty at the end of every Round to keep battling. Each Round 1 more success is required.

Move.Name: Hex
Move.Description: The user casts a terrible hex over the target, the effects will be greater if the target is vulnerable.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If the Target is affected by a Status Ailment add 2 Extra Dice to the Damage Pool.

Move.Name: Lick
Move.Description: The user licks the foe. The saliva can numb the body of most creatures.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 3 Chance Dice to Paralyze the Foe.

Move.Name: Moongeist Beam
Move.Description: A cold reflection of the moon shines upon the target, it doesn't hurt physically but those who stare directly into the light simply collapse.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. If anything on the foe's side would prevent this move from dealing damage (Pokémon Type, Abilities, Shield Moves, Weather or Barriers) ignore it. This Move cannot be Clashed.

Move.Name: Night Shade
Move.Description: The user casts a shade with a frightening mirage inside that torments the target.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll Damage Dice according to the User's Rank. 1 Dice at Starter Rank. 2 Dice at Beginner Rank.  3 dice at Amateur Rank.  4 Dice at Ace Rank.  5 Dice at Professional Rank. Ignores Defense.

Move.Name: Nightmare
Move.Description: The user enters the target's dream to torment it.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Will only work if the Target is asleep. Deal 1 Damage to the foe. Deal 1 Damage again at the beginning of each Round if the target is still asleep.

Move.Name: Ominous Wind
Move.Description: The Pokemon sends out a goosebump-inducing, repulsive wind that might make the user feel an evil rush.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 1 Chance Dice to Increase the User's Strength, Dexterity, Special, Defense, and Sp. Defense.

Move.Name: Phantom Force
Move.Description: The Pokemon disappears into a dark dimension to infiltrate even the most impenetrable defenses. It may reappear during its next action.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Charge Move. While charging this Move, other Moves will not affect the user. If the Target made a Shielding Action the shield is destroyed and won't have any effect.

Move.Name: Shadow Ball
Move.Description: The Pokemon hurls a sphere made of shadow and dark matter to harm the foe.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 1 Chance Dice to Reduce foe's Sp. Defense.

Move.Name: Shadow Bone
Move.Description: The bone that this Pokemon uses as a weapon contains a spirit, that spirit may cling onto a victim, creating openings for its master.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 2 Chance Dice to Reduce the Foe's Defense.

Move.Name: Shadow Claw
Move.Description: Claws become semi-ethereal and are able to briefly pierce armor, hide, skin, and objects so it can strike the target on any weak spot.
Move.AdditionalInfo: High Critical.

Move.Name: Shadow Force
Move.Description: The Pokemon disappears into a dark dimension to strike its foe at the next opportunity. The blow will hurt the target not on their body but directly on their soul.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. Charge Move. While charging this Move, other Move will not affect the user. If the Target made a Shielding Action, the shield is destroyed and won't have any effect. Damage dealt by this Move cannot be healed for 24 hrs

Move.Name: Shadow Punch
Move.Description: The Pokemon punches through its own shadow. The attack comes out from the foe's shadows as if it were a portal.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Fist Based. Never Fail.

Move.Name: Shadow Sneak
Move.Description: The user sneaks through darkness and strikes out of the target's shadow. The Pokemon can move freely inside shades as if it were incorporeal.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Priority 1.

Move.Name: Spectral Thief
Move.Description: Through the shadows, the user sneaks on its target to steal its life force and consume it, leaving the victim with a sense of grief and loss.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If successful, BEFORE the user deals damage with this Move, steal all Attribute Increases the foe may have. Reduced Attributes on the foe remain.

Move.Name: Spirit Shackle
Move.Description: While attacking, the user sneakily binds its foe's shadow to the ground, restricting its movement and making it unable to escape.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Blocks.

Move.Name: Spite
Move.Description: The target feels overwhelmed by feelings of dread.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Reduce Target's Will to 1 point temporarily. Reset any effects it got from spending Will Points.

Move.Name: Trick-Or-Treat
Move.Description: The Pokemon takes the target Trick-or-Treating. The target gets a ghost costume which somehow cannot be removed without a medium's help.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Add the Ghost type to Target's Type. (ie. Meowth will now by Normal/Ghost Charizard will now be Fire/Flying/Ghost) If the Pokémon already has a third type attached, replace it.

Move.Name: Absorb
Move.Description: The user absorbs the vital energy of the foe.
Move.AdditionalInfo: The user restores HP equal to half the damage dealt rounded down.

Move.Name: Apple Acid
Move.Description: The Pokemon produces a sap from the tart apples it feeds on, if the apples, this sap is acidic and bad for your teeth.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Reduce the Foe's Sp. Defense.

Move.Name: Aromatherapy
Move.Description: The Pokemon releases medicinal scents and vapors to refresh the user and its allies.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Cure User and Allies from Burn, Freeze, Paralysis, Poison, or Sleep.

Move.Name: Branch Poke
Move.Description: The Pokemon rudely starts poking its foe with a stick.

Move.Name: Bullet Seed
Move.Description: The Pokemon shoots seeds rapidly as if they were bullets.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Successive Actions.

Move.Name: Cotton Guard
Move.Description: The user covers itself in cotton puffs that severely reduce the impact of physical attacks.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Increase the User's Defense by 3.

Move.Name: Cotton Spore
Move.Description: The Pokemon covers the foe in cotton, disrupting its movement speed.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Reduce foe's Dexterity by 2.

Move.Name: Drum Beating
Move.Description: The Pokemon has a perfectly good drum and you'd think it would use it. But it doesn't. It uses it's foe.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Reduce the Foe's Dexterity

Move.Name: Energy Ball
Move.Description: The Pokemon gathers nature's energy in a ball and hurls it at the foe. Trees and bushes may be left opaque and sad.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 1 Chance Dice to Reduce foe's Sp. Defense.

Move.Name: Forest's Curse
Move.Description: The user calls the forest to lay a curse upon the target, making it grow vines and vegetation around its whole body. The curse will not be easily lifted without a medium's help.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Add the Grass Type to the Target's Type (ie. Nidoran will now be Poison/Grass Heracross will now be Bug/Fight/Grass). If the Pokémon already has a third type attached then replace it.

Move.Name: Frenzy Plant
Move.Description: The user roots down and calls the plants to grow in a frenzy around the foe, though it leaves the user exhausted.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Must Recharge.

Move.Name: Giga Drain
Move.Description: The Pokemon extracts a great amount of vital energy from the foe's body.
Move.AdditionalInfo: The user restores HP equal to half the damage dealt, rounded down.

Move.Name: Grass Knot
Move.Description: The user snares the target's feet with grass, making it fall to the ground. The bigger the foe the harder the fall.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Add 1 Extra Dice to the Damage Pool for every 50 kgs. of weight on the foe, up to +4 Extra Dice.

Move.Name: Grass Pledge
Move.Description: The Pokemon chants to invoke the power of Grass. Its pledge is heard then then soil trembles and the ground crumbles as vegetation rises to grapple anyone in the field.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Reduce the Dexterity of those affected.

Move.Name: Grass Whistle
Move.Description: The user plays a beautiful and soothing melody that lulls the target into a peaceful sleep.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Sound Based. Put the Target to Sleep.

Move.Name: Grassy Terrain
Move.Description: The Pokemon calls upon the healing power of nature to grow a patch of miraculous grass on its side of the battlefield.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If successful, spend 1 Will point to activate. Everyone in the user's side of the field heals 1 HP at the end of each round. Add 1 Extra Dice to the Damage Rolls of Grass Type Moves.

Move.Name: Grav Apple
Move.Description: The Pokemon rises on top of its foe and drops an apple on their head. The foe proceeds to eat the apple, distracting it from the fight.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Reduce the Foe's Defense.

Move.Name: Horn Leech
Move.Description: The user rams the foe and absorbs some of its vital energy with its horns.
Move.AdditionalInfo: The User restores HP equal to half the damage dealt, rounded down.

Move.Name: Ingrain
Move.Description: The Pokemon roots itself to the ground, absorbing the nutrients and recovering health.
Move.AdditionalInfo: User Heals 1 HP at the end of every Round. While this move is active the User is now Blocked.

Move.Name: Leaf Blade
Move.Description: The Pokemon uses the sharp leaves on its body to cut through the foe.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. High Critical.

Move.Name: Leaf Storm
Move.Description: A furious storm of sharp leaves swirls and pierces the target. The user is left exhausted.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Reduce the User's Special by 2.

Move.Name: Leaf Tornado
Move.Description: A bush worth of sharp leaves swirls around the foe making it harder for it to aim attacks properly.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 5 Chance Dice to Reduce the Foe's Accuracy.

Move.Name: Leafage
Move.Description: The user throws leaf darts towards its foe.

Move.Name: Leech Seed
Move.Description: The user plants some seeds on the target, the seeds sprout and restore the user's health by absorbing the foe's vital energy.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If successful spend 1 Will point to activate. At the end of each Round, Roll 1 Dice of Damage to the foe. User heals for 1 HP for every damage dealt this way. Grass Type Pokemon are immune to this Move.

Move.Name: Magical Leaf
Move.Description: The user sends out a floating leaf that will pursue the target until it hits.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Never Fail.

Move.Name: Mega Drain
Move.Description: The user absorbs a big amount of vital energy from the target.
Move.AdditionalInfo: The user restores HP equal to half the damage dealt, rounded down.

Move.Name: Needle Arm
Move.Description: The Pokemon hits the foe with its flailing arms, some thorns may get stuck on the target like needles.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 3 Chance Dice to Flinch the Foe.

Move.Name: Petal Blizzard
Move.Description: The Pokemon showers the battlefield with a raging blizzard of petals and leaves, anyone close to the user will suffer the consequences.

Move.Name: Petal Dance
Move.Description: The Pokemon starts swirling petals around in a true display of nature's power, the petals are guided by the wind to strike the foe.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Rampage.

Move.Name: Power Whip
Move.Description: The Pokemon violently lashes the foe with its vines or a part of its body, acting as a powerful whip.

Move.Name: Razor Leaf
Move.Description: The Pokemon shoots one or more sharp leaves that cut through all targets as if they were razors.
Move.AdditionalInfo: High Critical.

Move.Name: Sappy Seed
Move.Description: From a magical bean, the user grows a cute stalk that will attach itself to the nearest target. Once it ingrains, it will grow and grow and grow until it reaches the sky.
Move.AdditionalInfo: At the end of the Round, Roll 1 Die of Damage to the foe. Restore 1 HP to the user for every damage dealt this way. If the user of this Move is at its Final Stage of Evolution, this move fails.

Move.Name: Seed Bomb
Move.Description: The user throws a big seed that explodes on contact with the foe.

Move.Name: Seed Flare
Move.Description: Shaymin releases an explosion of pollen and seeds that the foe cannot shake off, leaving it vulnerable. Over time, these seeds will grow into gigantic trees of life.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. Roll 4 Chance Dice to Reduce the foe's Sp. Defense by 2.

Move.Name: Sleep Powder
Move.Description: The user scatters powder around, anyone who comes in contact with it will fall asleep.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Put the Target to Sleep.

Move.Name: Snap Trap
Move.Description: The user is so flat that you can barely see it in the tall grass, it is just waiting for its foe to get close enough to use its body as a snare trap.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Target is Blocked for the Next 4 Rounds.

Move.Name: Solar Beam
Move.Description: The user focuses the sunlight it has absorbed into a powerful and devastating beam of light.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Charge Move. If there is a Sunny Weather, you skip this Move's Charge action. If performed under Rain, Sandstorm, or Hail Weather, this Move takes two actions to Charge.

Move.Name: Solar Blade
Move.Description: The Pokemon focuses the sunlight on its sharp leaves, then releases the energy with a shattering block.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Charge Move. If there is a Sunny Weather, you skip this Move's Charge action. If performed under Rain, Sandstorm, or Hail Weather, this Move takes two actions to Charge.

Move.Name: Spiky Shield
Move.Description: The Pokemon covers itself with a thorn filled shell, the foe will be damaged if it hits directly into it.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Priority 3. Shield. Reduce 3 Damage Dice from the next attack and deal 2 Damage Dice to the attacker if it used a physical non-ranged Move.

Move.Name: Spore
Move.Description: A powerful somniferous spore that is shot at the target to make it fall asleep.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Put the Target to Sleep.

Move.Name: Strength Sap
Move.Description: The Pokemon looks for a weak spot on its foe, then feeds on its vital energy. The foe is left feeling feeble.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Reduce Foe's Strength. User Heals HP equal to the Foe's Current Strength Score. Healing in-battle limitations apply.

Move.Name: Stun Spore
Move.Description: A blow of dust that paralyzes the target on the spot and cramps its muscles.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Paralyze the Foe.

Move.Name: Synthesis
Move.Description: The Pokemon uses the sunlight as energy to regain its vitality.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Basic Heal. If Successful spend 1 Will point to activate. If performed under Sunny weather this Move is a Complete Heal. If Rain/Sandstorm Weather is in effect this move only heals 1 HP.

Move.Name: Trop Kick
Move.Description: The user strikes with an intense and alluring kick.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Reduce Foe's Strength.

Move.Name: Vine Whip
Move.Description: They Pokemon uses its slender vines as a whip against the foe. They are as long as 20 feet.

Move.Name: Wood Hammer
Move.Description: The Pokemon recklessly slams the foe with a part of its rugged body, the user also gets hurt in the process.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Recoil.

Move.Name: Worry Seed
Move.Description: The user plants a seed in its foe. It causes a restless preoccupation that won't let it sleep at night.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Until the end of the Scene. Target's Ability is now "Insomnia".

Move.Name: Bone Club
Move.Description: The user hits the target with a bone, the smack may leave a bump on the target's head.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 2 Chance Dice to Flinch the Foe.

Move.Name: Bone Rush
Move.Description: The user quickly strikes the foe with a bone, one blow after another.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Successive Actions.

Move.Name: Bonemerang
Move.Description: The Pokemon throws a bone to hit the foe. The bone returns like a boomerang, striking a second time.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Double Action.

Move.Name: Bulldoze
Move.Description: The user stomps and tramples the place, breaking stones, trees, and everything nearby.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Reduce the Dexterity of those affected.

Move.Name: Dig
Move.Description: The user digs a tunnel on the ground and attacks while coming out from below.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Charge Move. While charging this move, the User will be out of range. Can be hit by Earthquake, Magnitude, or a similar move.

Move.Name: Drill Run
Move.Description: The user rotates its body imitating a drill and crashes against the foe. This attack may pierce through walls and floors with ease and great precision.
Move.AdditionalInfo: High Critical.

Move.Name: Earth Power
Move.Description: The user sends out a subterranean wave that bursts on the ground bellow the target. It looks like the earth molds to the Pokemon's will.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 1 Chance Dice to Reduce the foe's Sp. Defense.

Move.Name: Earthquake
Move.Description: The Pokemon focuses its energy into shaking the ground, everyone around will be thrown like a rag doll.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Area Attack.

Move.Name: Fissure
Move.Description: The user tears the ground apart in a monstrous display of force. If the foe falls through the fissure it might need a rescue team to get it out.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Deal damage to the Target equal to their remaining HP plus 1 lethal damage.

Move.Name: High Horsepower
Move.Description: The Pokemon rushes towards its target and tramples it without mercy.

Move.Name: Land's Wrath
Move.Description: The earth moves on its own, no attacker in sight. The floor crumbles and the ground shakes while engulfing its victims. From the rubble, lush trees emerge a short time after.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal.  All Foes in Range.

Move.Name: Magnitude
Move.Description: The user quakes the ground plates. Some plates will move easier than others.
Move.AdditionalInfo: 1 Dice to determine this Move's Power

Move.Name: Mud Bomb
Move.Description: The Pokemon shoots a ball made of mud that bursts on the target, some mud may get on its eyes.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 3 Chance Dice to Reduce the Foe's Accuracy.

Move.Name: Mud Shot
Move.Description: The Pokemon shoots a stream of mud that covers the foe, obstructing its movement.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Reduce the Foe's Dexterity.

Move.Name: Mud Slap
Move.Description: The user hurls some mud to the face of the foe, leaving it unable to see clearly.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Reduce the foe's Accuracy.

Move.Name: Mud Sport
Move.Description: The user covers everything with mud, reducing the effectiveness of electric attacks made on the field.
Move.AdditionalInfo: For the next 4 Rounds Electric Type attacks won't add their Power to the Damage Pool.

Move.Name: Precipice Blades
Move.Description: Giant blades emerge from the earth with every step of the user. If you fall into them, they are almost impossible to survive.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal.

Move.Name: Rototiller
Move.Description: The Pokemon digs around and moves the soil to make it ideal for plant growth.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Increase the Strength and Special of all Grass Type Pokémon in the battlefield.

Move.Name: Sand Attack
Move.Description: The user shoots some sand into the opponent's eyes.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Reduce the foe's Accuracy.

Move.Name: Sand Tomb
Move.Description: The Pokemon creates a shifting sand pit around the foe, leaving it unable to escape.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Block. Roll 2 Dice of Damage against the foe at the end of every Round. Lasts 4 Rounds.

Move.Name: Shore Up
Move.Description: The Pokemon gathers the sand around itself to restore its body to shape.
