Move.AdditionalInfo: This Move only works if the foe just used an attack. Roll the same Damage Pool as your foe's last attack and add 2 Extra Damage Dice.

Move.Name: Metal Claw
Move.Description: The Pokémon attacks using its sharp claws, the friction may leave them even sharper.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 1 Chance Dice to Increase the user's Strength.

Move.Name: Metal Sound
Move.Description: The user produces a horrible noise that impedes the foe from focusing on the fight, leaving it vulnerable to attacks.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Sound Based. Reduce the foe's Special Defense by 2.

Move.Name: Meteor Mash
Move.Description: The user charges with a strong fist and strikes like a meteor.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Fist Based. Roll 2 Chance Dice to Increase the User's Strength.

Move.Name: Mirror Shot
Move.Description: The user dazes the foe with a beam of light. Those who have experienced it describe it as
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 3 Chance Dice to Confuse the foe.

Move.Name: Shift Gear
Move.Description: The Pokémon has its gears rotate quickly,. Working like a powerful machine.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Increase the User's Strength by 1 and Dexterity by 2.

Move.Name: Smart Strike
Move.Description: The user stabs the foe using one of its sharp horns with astounding precision, the resulting wound will be very deep and must be treated immediately.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. Never Fail.

Move.Name: Steel Beam
Move.Description: A concentrated ray of light that is capable of melting even the thickest steel plates. Unfortunately the user will also have trouble handling this power.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Recoil.

Move.Name: Steel Wing
Move.Description: The Pokémon uses its sharp feathers as if they were razors.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 1 Chance Dice to Increase the User's Defense.

Move.Name: Sunsteel Strike
Move.Description: You suddenly stop your in tracks as you see a bright and blinding light coming towards you at great speed. You did not see what hit you and then it's all darkness.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. If anything on the foe's side of the field would prevent this move from dealing damage (Pokemon types. Abilities. Shield Moves. Weather. Or Barriers.) ignore it. This Move cannot be Clashed.

Move.Name: Aqua Jet
Move.Description: The user propels itself with a blast of water and strikes at high speed.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Priority 1.

Move.Name: Aqua Ring
Move.Description: The user coats itself in a ring of special flowing water that lessens the pain.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If successful spent 1 Will point to activate. At the end of each Round, recover 1 HP. Lasts 4 Rounds.

Move.Name: Aqua Tail
Move.Description: The user swings its tail as if it were a vicious wave in a raging storm.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 3 Chance Dice to Flinch the foe.

Move.Name: Bouncy Bubble
Move.Description: The user shoots bubbles at its target, the bubbles fill up with fresh water upon contact and bounce back towards the user. Should you drink the water inside? Who cares? It's fun!
Move.AdditionalInfo: The user restores HP equal to half the damage dealt, rounded down. If the user of this Move is at its Final Stage of Evolution, this move fails.

Move.Name: Brine
Move.Description: The user blasts the foe with extremely dense water, if the target is tired he may be swept away easily by the pressure.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If the foe is at half HP or less, add 3 Extra Dice to the Damage Pool.

Move.Name: Bubble
Move.Description: A spray of bubbles flies around the enemies, some of the bubbles stick to their bodies hindering their movement.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Target all foes in range. Roll 1 Chance Dice to Reduce the Dexterity of those affected.

Move.Name: Bubble Beam
Move.Description: A long stream of bubbles hits the foe, the bubble foam may prevent the target from moving freely.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 1 Chance Dice to Reduce the foe's Dexterity.

Move.Name: Clamp
Move.Description: The user traps and crushes the opponent using its thick and sturdy shell.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Block. Deal 2 Dice of Damage at the end of each Round. Lasts 4 Rounds.

Move.Name: Crabhammer
Move.Description: A large pincer strikes with the power of a hammer. The demolition power is incredible.
Move.AdditionalInfo: High Critical.

Move.Name: Dive
Move.Description: The user submerges into the water and continues diving at an insane speed.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Charge Move. While charging this move, the User will be out of range. Allows the Pokémon to swim into Deep Waters.

Move.Name: Fishious Rend
Move.Description: This Pokémon uses its gills to snap at its target, even if they don't have teeth, they can have a crushing strength.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If the foe has not had its Turn this Round, Add 2 Extra Dice to the Damage Pool.

Move.Name: Hydro Cannon
Move.Description: The Pokémon blasts the foe with a water surge that could bring down a house. The user needs to res afterwards.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Must Recharge.

Move.Name: Hydro Pump
Move.Description: The user builds up pressure inside its body and then releases a tremendous amount of water at the target.

Move.Name: Life Dew
Move.Description: The user creates a fresh-water dew that makes it and its allies full of energy.
Move.AdditionalInfo: If successful, spend 1 Will point to activate. User and Allies in Range heal 1 HP at the end of each Round. Lasts 4 Rounds.

Move.Name: Liquidation
Move.Description: The Pokémon gets close to its foe then strikes while bursting a full-force blast of pressurized water, the water may cut or dent through the foe's armor.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. Roll 2 Chance Dice to Reduce the Foe's Defense.

Move.Name: Muddy Water
Move.Description: The user fills its mouth with dirt and spits a torrent of mud at the foes. This mud may get in the eyes of the enemies.
Move.AdditionalInfo: All Foes in Range. Roll 3 Chance Dice to Reduce the Accuracy of those affected.

Move.Name: Octazooka
Move.Description: The user sprays ink at the target's face to obstruct its vison.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 5 Chance Dice to Reduce the foe's Accuracy.

Move.Name: Origin Pulse
Move.Description: The Pokémon sends a giant pulse underwater that creates a chain reaction and causes water to move in large streams. It is believed that all water in the sea moves thanks to this.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal.

Move.Name: Rain Dance
Move.Description: The user performs a curious mystic dance that summons a heavy rainfall.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Rain Weather is activated for the next 4 Rounds.

Move.Name: Razor Shell
Move.Description: The Pokémon uses its sharp shell as a weapon to cut the target's fur, armor or anything protecting its body.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 1 Chance Dice to Reduce the foe's Defense.

Move.Name: Scald
Move.Description: The user shoots a torrent of boiling water, it may leave the foe sopping with burns.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 3 Chance Dice to Burn the foe.

Move.Name: Snipe Shot
Move.Description: The User Shoots a piercing water jet with incredible precision.
Move.AdditionalInfo: High Critical. Ignore effects from Moves or Abilities that would prevent this Move from targeting a foe.

Move.Name: Soak
Move.Description: The user shoots a stream of water and moisture that clings to the foe's body as an overcoat.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Change the target's Type to Water.

Move.Name: Sparkling Aria
Move.Description: The Pokémon sings a beautiful melody, the song comes out as a sparkling fountain, bursting upon impact and quenching any fire in its path.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Sound Based. Area Attack. If an affected Pokémon had any of the Burn Status Conditions, heal it instead of dealing damage.

Move.Name: Splishy Splash
Move.Description: The Pokémon rides a giant surge of electricity as if surfing. It looks incredibly rad but it is also dangerous, as electricity does not share the same properties of water for safe surfing.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 3 Chance Dice to Paralyze the foe. If the user of this Move is at its Final Stage of Evolution, this move fails.

Move.Name: Steam Eruption
Move.Description: In less than a second, the sound of steam boiling over a raging engine thunders through the ears of the foe before it is shot through the sky by a scalding geyser.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Lethal. Roll 3 Chance Dice to Apply Burn 2 to those affected.

Move.Name: Surf
Move.Description: A giant wave of water sweeps the area while the user swims on top of it.

Move.Name: Water Gun
Move.Description: The user learns to shoot water with enough force to hurt the foe.

Move.Name: Water Pledge
Move.Description: The Pokémon chants to invoke the power of Water. Moisture in the air bends the light to create an inspiring rainbow. Everyone in the field is sure to give its best.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Creates a rainbow that adds 2 Dice to all Chance Dice rolls. This effect lasts 4 turns.

Move.Name: Water Pulse
Move.Description: The Pokémon attacks with a pulsing blast of water, this leaves the foe feeling dizzy.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 3 Chance Dice to Confuse the foe.

Move.Name: Water Shuriken
Move.Description: The Pokémon quickly throws sharp jets of water in the shape of a shuriken.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Priority 1. Successive Actions.

Move.Name: Water Sport
Move.Description: The user soaks the battlefield with moisture, making it harder for fire attacks to ignite.
Move.AdditionalInfo: For the next 4 Rounds Fire Type attacks won't add their Power to the Damage Pool.

Move.Name: Water Spout
Move.Description: The Pokémon builds up an amazing pressure and releases a huge columnar vortex of water that could even reach the clouds.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Remove 1 Dice of Damage for every missing HP of the User. Up to 5 Dice may be reduced this way.

Move.Name: Waterfall
Move.Description: The Pokémon may swim with such strength that it may even swim upwards in a waterfall.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll 3 Chance Dice to Flinch the foe.

Move.Name: Whirlpool
Move.Description: Trap the foe inside a violent swirling whirlpool that makes the foe unable to escape the battle.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Block. Deal 2 dice of damage at the end of each Round. Lasts 4 Rounds.

Move.Name: Withdraw
Move.Description: The user hides inside its hard shell to protect itself from incoming attacks.
Move.AdditionalInfo: Increase User's Defense.

Move.Name: Any Move
Move.AdditionalInfo: This move represents every possible move. Metronome but better.

Move.Name: Struggle (Physical)
Move.AdditionalInfo: The most basic attack.

Move.Name: Struggle (Special)
Move.AdditionalInfo: The most basic attack.

Move.Name: Grapple
Move.AdditionalInfo: The foe is Blocked. Foe can resist this Maneuver by rolling their Strength or Dexterity score and scoring the same or more successes than the user.

Move.Name: Help Another
Move.AdditionalInfo: Roll your Accuracy as if it was Chance Dice. If Successful, add one die to the Action of an Ally. Up to 6 dice may be added this way.

Move.Name: Cover An Ally
Move.AdditionalInfo: The user will provide cover to the target from  attacks and is more likely to be hit by close-range attacks. The level of Cover the user provides will depend on its size.

Move.Name: Stabilize An Ally
Move.AdditionalInfo: The User applies CPR and/or first aid to an unconcious Ally. Target won't receive Lethal Damage each hour anymore. Each Lethal Damage on the Ally reduces 1 Success to the Accuracy Pool of this Maneuver.

Move.Name: Run Away
Move.AdditionalInfo: The User runs away from the battlefield. This effect ends the battle. Foes might try to prevent this by rolling: Dexterity + Athletic and scoring the same or more successes. If the user is Blocked this Maneuver fails.
